The good news I found the failing logic in the  Euca Windows Service on w2k8. 

On an instance restart, the code in EucaServiceLibrary.cs 
is not being ran because the flag "JustLauched" is false in DoBootstrapThreadedRun() 


 //// create a partiton and format ephemeral storage

            if (EucaConstant.JustLaunched)
            {
                try
                {
                    int format = (int)EucaUtil.GetRegistryValue(
                        Registry.LocalMachine, Bootstrapper.EucaRegistryPath, "FormatDrives");
                    if (format == 1)
                    {
                        EucaLogger.Debug("Attempting to initialize attached disks");


Thus, in Windows we can't distinguish between warm reboot from the instance
( shutdown /r ) and a restart, so we don't want to re-format the ephemeral
every time since there may be valid data there in a warm start path.

We know where the problem area is now.
